      "role": "user",
      "content": "that seems a bit biased. you're basically saying the moral argument is the \"correct\" foundation and the economic concerns are just about bad implementation. but what about the actual math? if a government system is inherently less efficient than a competitive market, isn't the \"inefficient takeover\" argument actually the one more grounded in reality?",
